  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Beauregard is in the charming Savoyard resort of La Clusaz, located at the foot of the slopes with a ski lift outside the hotel front door. With ski in and out access, it is an excellent base for exploring the ski domain, and with a wellness area including an indoor pool, it ticks all the boxes for a winter getaway.</p>
<h2>A hotel at the foot of the ski slopes</h2>
<p>With ski in and out access, this cosy and contemporary hotel gives you convenient access to the slopes each day. The hotel is also only a couple of minutes walk into <a data-udi="umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9}" title="La Clusaz">La Clusaz</a> centre, which has a variety of shops, bars and restaurants, making it a perfect choice for any couple, family and group.</p>
<p><span>Built in the traditional Savoyard chalet style, the rooms are</span><span> elegantly decorated offering you a cosy place to stay. All of the bedrooms benefit from having beautiful views of the Aravis mountains, which you can enjoy from your private balcony. </span></p>
<h2>Cosy lounge</h2>
<p>The bar and lounge area is the perfect place to relax with a drink or one of the speciality cocktails after a day on the slopes, cosy up next to the fireplace for a night in and enjoy an aperitif before your evening meal. </p>
<p>Each evening you can enjoy a three course meal which is influenced by the seasons, dishes are carefully selected and prepared by the talented kitchen team who pride themselves on excellent taste and presentation. The restaurant has lovely big windows so you can really take in the amazing views over the snowy mountains. </p>
<h2>Soothing spa</h2>
<div>After a day of skiing or snowboarding, come back to the hotel to relax in the hotels own wellness area. Soak away your achy ski legs in the steam room or sauna, or take a dip in the indoor pool. The Hotel Au Coeur du Village, just next door, offers a range of treatments including massages so you can fully unwind after a day of exploring La Clusaz, treatments can be booked and paid for locally.</div>
<div></div>]]></description>
